10. “As it turns to walk back into the jungle, a final, low growl: ‘Thank you for not forcing my hand. The flame is hungry today. I am glad it did not eat. Come back with fruit. We will share. Maybe.’”

Thank‑you note: Dearest Fu‑Kong, Burning Sentinel, you magnificent, spear‑wielding, verdant‑flamed guardian of the sacred grove. I thank you for not impaling me with your Emberwood Spear while I documented every glowing vein in your jet-black fur. Your chest-beat made my heart skip, and your green-yellow flames are the most beautiful fire I have ever seen—the kind that heals rather than destroys. You are not a monster; you are a tree’s last prayer given fists and a roar. I will never look at a volcanic jungle the same way again. May your Ember-Mites keep your flames balanced, may your spear never dull, and may the poachers always burn before they reach your grove. With verdant admiration, your chronicler.

